"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.6\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.6</span> 標題：邊界牆、圍牆、圍欄、柵欄（boundary wall, fence）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： גְּבוּל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： gvul)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:12\">EZK 40:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:12\">EZK 40:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:13\">EZK 43:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:17\">EZK 43:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:20\">EZK 43:20</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： גדר, גָּדֵר, גֶּדֶר, גְּדֵרָה, גְּדֶרֶת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： gadar（動詞）, gader, geder, gderah, gdereth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:24\">NUM 22:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:24\">NUM 22:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:9\">EZR 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:8\">JOB 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:4\">PSA 62:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:13\">PSA 80:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:41\">PSA 89:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:31\">PRO 24:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:8\">ECC 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:5\">ISA 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:3\">JER 49:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:7\">LAM 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:9\">LAM 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:5\">EZK 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:5\">EZK 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:30\">EZK 22:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:30\">EZK 22:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:7\">EZK 42:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:10\">EZK 42:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:12\">EZK 42:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:8\">HOS 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:8\">HOS 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:11\">MIC 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:17\">NAM 3:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חוֹמָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： chomah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:7\">LAM 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:5\">EZK 40:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:20\">EZK 42:20</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חַיִץ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： chayits)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:10\">EZK 13:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מְסוּכָה, מְשֻׂכָה, מְשׂוּכָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： msukah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:19\">PRO 15:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:5\">ISA 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:4\">MIC 7:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： קִיר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： qir)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:4\">PSA 62:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שׂוך</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： suk（動詞）)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:10\">JOB 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:8\">HOS 2:8</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שׁוּר, שׁוּרָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： shur, shurah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:22\">GEN 49:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:11\">JOB 24:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ἀνάλημμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： analēmma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir50:2\">SIR 50:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： μεσότοιχον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： mesotoichon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14\">EPH 2:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： τεῖχος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： teichos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:60\">1MA 4:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc6:7\">1MA 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc6:62\">1MA 6:62</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc9:54\">1MA 9:54</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： τοῖχος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： toichos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:3\">ACT 23:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob2:9\">TOB 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob2:10\">TOB 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis13:15\">WIS 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir14:24\">SIR 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir22:17\">SIR 22:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir23:18\">SIR 23:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd6:8\">1ES 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Odes10:5\">ODA 10:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： φραγμός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： fragmos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33\">MAT 21:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:1\">MRK 12:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:23\">LUK 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14\">EPH 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir36:25\">SIR 36:25</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0415_fence.jpg\" alt=\"石圍欄\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">石圍欄 (© بدارين, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>圍欄是用來圍住某個區域的構築物。在以色列地，圍欄通常是用石頭做的，少數是用樹枝和灌木做的（僅作臨時構築物）。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>許多社會都用某種類型的籬笆、圍牆或障礙物來把田地圍起來。在某些情況下，籬笆是由原木或樹枝堆砌而成，還有些情況是由夯實的泥土或堆疊的石頭做成。然而，這裡的重點不是「籬笆」的形式，而是它的功能，因此翻譯者可能常常要使用描述性的短語；例如，「圍住田地的障礙物」，或「防止動物進入田地的障礙物」。由於石頭在以色列地很常見，那裡的籬笆通常是用一些鬆散放置的石塊堆成的。在許多文化中，這種石頭構築物被稱為「牆」，而不是「籬笆」。</p>\n<p>希伯來文<em>gvul</em> 通常是指「邊界」（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.7 地界、界標 (boundary marker)&lt;REALIA:3.7&gt;</a> ），這個詞在《以西結書》中出現過幾次，意思略有不同。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:12\">EZK 40:12</a> 中，它似乎指的是「矮牆」（“low wall”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）、「欄杆」（“railing”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ），或僅僅是指「障礙物」（“barrier[s]”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> ）。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:13\">EZK 43:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:17\">EZK 43:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:20\">EZK 43:20</a> 中，該詞是指祭壇底部及各層周圍的某種「邊」（“rim”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> ）。</p>\n<p>有些語言會用不同的詞語表示建築物的外牆與分隔房間的內牆。希伯來文<em>chomah</em> 通常指外牆，尤其是城牆（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.13.3.1 城牆、外郭、城垛 (city wall, rampart, battlement)&lt;REALIA:3.13.3.1&gt;</a> ），但本條目列出的經文除外。其他希伯來文詞語既可指內牆，也可指外牆，翻譯者要根據上下文來確定詞語正確的意思。希臘文<em>toichos</em> 指內牆。在翻譯時，房子的外牆可稱為「房子的側面」，而內牆則可稱為「房子裡面的隔牆」。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:10\">EZK 13:10</a> ：在這節經文中，希伯來文<em>chayits</em> 表示「分隔物」，是一面臨時的、不太堅固的牆。很多譯本通過添加修飾語來指出這一點，比如「搖晃的」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ）、「不結實的」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Living Bible (1971)\">LB</abbr> ）、「脆弱的」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> ）、「不穩的」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Spanish Common Language Version (Dios Habla Hoy)\">SPCL</abbr> ），或「鬆散石塊堆砌的」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> ）。</p>\n<p>人們對希伯來文<em>shur</em> 和<em>shurah</em> 這兩個詞有多種理解。詞語的字面意思是「行列」，可以指一排石頭、一堵牆，或一道籬笆。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:22\">GEN 49:22</a> 中，大多數譯本都譯為「牆」（“wall”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"French Common Language Version (Bible en français courant)\">FRCL</abbr> ）。然而，在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:11\">JOB 24:11</a> 中，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 把<em>shurah</em> 譯為“olive rows”（「一排排橄欖樹」）。如《〈約伯記〉手冊》（<em>A Handbook on The Book of Job</em> ）所指出的，這可能不是文本的意思。在中東，橄欖樹通常生長在特別開墾的梯田上。梯田本身用擋土牆來支撐，<em>shurah</em> 在這裡可能就是指擋土牆。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Revised Standard Version (1989)\">NRSV</abbr> 沒有採用<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 的譯法，而是譯成「梯田」（“terraces”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 同）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> 譯為「花園」，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Standard Bible\">NASB</abbr> 譯為「牆」（“walls”）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 選擇不翻譯這個詞。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14\">EPH 2:14</a> 中，希臘文<em>mesotoichon</em> 和<em>fragmos</em> 喻指律法，它是猶太人和外邦人之間的屏障，是「分隔的牆」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直譯）。在本節經文中，這兩個詞可以譯為「隔斷的牆」或「分開的牆」。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
